  "bib_entries": {
    "208003238": {
      "title": "Herding cats: Modelling, simulation, testing, and data-mining for weak memory",
      "abstract": "There is a joke where a physicist and a mathematician are asked to herd cats. The physicist starts with an infinitely large pen which he reduces until it is of reasonable diameter yet contains all the cats. The mathematician builds a fence around himself and declares the outside to be the inside. Defining memory models is akin to herding cats: both the physicist's or mathematician's attitudes are tempting, but neither can go without the other."
    }
